4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE OFFENSE OF
5 ENDANGERING THE WELFARE OF CHILDREN; PROVIDING THAT IT IS AN OFFENSE TO COMMIT
6 CERTAIN CRIMES RELATED TO PARTNER OR FAMILY MEMBER ASSAULT IN THE PRESENCE OF A
7 CHILD; PROVIDING A PENALTY; AMENDING SECTION 45-5-622, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
8 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 45-5-622, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "45-5-622. Endangering welfare of children. (1) (a) A parent, guardian, or other person supervising
14 the welfare of a child less than 18 years old commits the offense of endangering the welfare of children if the
15 parent, guardian, or other person knowingly endangers the child's welfare by violating a duty of care, protection,
16 or support.
17 (b) A parent or guardian of a child does not violate a duty of care, protection, or support by
18 permitting the child to engage in independent activities consistent with the child's intellectual, emotional, and
19 physical maturity, including:
20 (i) traveling to and from school by walking, running, bicycling, public transit, or other means;
21 (ii) traveling to and from nearby commercial or recreational facilities;
22 (iii) engaging in outdoor play;
23 (iv) remaining for less than 15 minutes in a vehicle if the temperature inside the vehicle is not or will
24 not become dangerously hot or cold;
25 (v) remaining at home if the parent or guardian:
26 (A) returns home the same day on which the parent or guardian gives the child permission to
27 remain at home;
28 (B) makes provisions for the child to contact the parent or guardian; and
