1 (C) makes provisions for any reasonably foreseeable emergency.
2 (2) Except as provided in 16-6-305, a parent or guardian or any person who is 18 years of age or
3 older, whether or not the parent, guardian, or other person is supervising the welfare of the child, commits the
4 offense of endangering the welfare of children if the parent, guardian, or other person knowingly contributes to
5 the delinquency of a child less than:
6 (a) 18 years old by:
7 (i) supplying or encouraging the use of an intoxicating substance by the child; or
8 (ii) assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to enter a place of prostitution; or
9 (b) 16 years old by assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to:
10 (i) abandon the child's place of residence without the consent of the child's parents or guardian; or
11 (ii) engage in sexual conduct.
12 (3) A person, whether or not the person is supervising the welfare of a child less than 18 years of
13 age, commits the offense of endangering the welfare of children if the person, in the residence of a child, in a
14 building, structure, conveyance, or outdoor location where a child might reasonably be expected to be present,
15 in a room offered to the public for overnight accommodation, or in any multiple-unit residential building,
16 knowingly:
17 (a) produces or manufactures methamphetamine or attempts to produce or manufacture
18 methamphetamine;
19 (b) possesses any material, compound, mixture, or preparation that contains any combination of
20 the items listed in 45-9-107 with intent to manufacture methamphetamine; or
21 (c) causes or permits a child to inhale, be exposed to, have contact with, or ingest
22 methamphetamine or be exposed to or have contact with methamphetamine paraphernalia.
23 (4) (a) A person commits the offense of endangering the welfare of a child if the person also
24 knowingly commits an offense identified in 45-5-202, 45-5-206, 45-5-213, or 45-5-215 against a partner or
25 family member in the presence of a child less than 18 years of age.
26 (b) For the purposes of this subsection (4), the following definitions apply:
27 (i) "Family member" has the same meaning as provided in 45-5-206.
28 (ii) "In the presence of a child" means in the physical presence of a child or having knowledge that
