4 (7) On the issue of whether there has been a violation of the duty of care, protection, and support,
5 the following, in addition to all other admissible evidence, is admissible: cruel treatment; abuse; infliction of
6 unnecessary and cruel punishment; abandonment; neglect; lack of proper medical care, clothing, shelter, and
7 food; and evidence of past bodily injury.
8 (8) The court may order, in its discretion, any fine levied or any bond forfeited upon a charge of
9 endangering the welfare of children paid to or for the benefit of the person or persons whose welfare the
10 defendant has endangered."
